<D>__{milady?}
<C>__{elizabeth}
<D>__{"your majesty", the first time. after that, "ma'am". not malm as in palm, mam as in ham. i'm informed your husband calls my husband bertie and my husband calls your husband lionel. i trust, however, you won't attempt to call me liz.}
<A>__{in the study: lionel stands listening, ear to the door.}
<C>__{bertie}
<D>__{how're they getting on?}
